br>
<br>
I play a mercenary in DAoC, and I've been keeping close tabs on how the developers plan to address the current weakness of the merc class.  Basically Mercenaries (and blademasters in Hybernia) have two big complaints.  <br>
<br>
1)  Mercs do less damage than a polearm-spec armsman, and they have much less defensive ability as well.  Dual wield does not currently work as intended.  <br>
<br>
The popular belief seems to be that Mythic will end up simply tweaking the dual wield formula upward until a merc outdamages an armsman as intended.  (should benifit infiltrators too).<br>
<br>
2)  Mercs have no skill that is not shared with another class in Albion.  Even our &quot;class&quot; skills are all given to other classes (dual wield and parry), and all other classes get these two skills before mercs do.  <br>
<br>
The most popular solution I have seen proposed to correct this is to add some sort of new skill exclusive to the mercenary class that would relate to the fact that mercenaries are members of the guild of shadows.  Most of the suggestions I have seen are basically similar versions of infiltrator skills.  Things such as &quot;sneak&quot; which would be a toned down, easier to see through, and temporary version of stealth, or perhaps some amount of ability to detect hidden.  Basically every suggestion I have seen along those lines was the type of skill that I imagine would cause an uproar amount the infiltrators that mercenaries were infringing upon their class skills.  <br>
<br>
I'm not necessarily in favor of giving a merc such a skill, I just wandered what you guys thought about it.  Personally, I'll just sit back and see what they do.  <br>
<br>
Mercs *are* members of the guild of shadows though.  From an RP standpoint (not necessarily a balance standpoint) it seems like they should have some sort of appropriate skill related to the Guild of Shadows.  <br>
