Yshae Mwitu<br>
Saracen Pugilist<br>
Master of the Mace<br>
Percival <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umaiyasamsara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maiya Samsara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 3:04:30 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do DAoC rogues feel about this?</span><hr size=1> Stealth is a rogue skill, not a skill you get for joining the Guild of Shadows. Scouts join the Defenders of Albion.<br>
<br>
Or do you suggest that Cabalists also should get stealth because they join the Guild of Shadows?<br>
<br>
It is the base class, not the guild that determines who gets stealth. So no, I do not think Mercs need and I definately have faith they will not get stealth. Albion already has 3 classes with stealth anyway, they don't need anymore.<br>
<br>
Adjusting dual wield will be sufficient to give the Mercs (and Blademasters of Hibernia) an appropriate place in their realms. The only other suggestion would be to give both Mercs and Blademasters a unique combat ability useable once per 7 minutes like the berserkers get.<br>
